Slate, the Internet-only magazine
owned by  Washington Post Co. (WPO) , promoted advertising executive
Matt Turck to the role of publisher.  Turck will start the job on Sept. 10, replacing John
Alderman, who is taking another position within the parent
company, Slate said today in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
